---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import Features from "../components/Features.astro";
import ScienceCard from "../components/ScienceCard.astro";
import Calculator from "../components/Calculator.astro";
import FAQ from "../components/FAQ.astro";
import { faqStructuredData, breadcrumbStructuredData } from "../lib/faq-data.js";
---

<Layout
  title="Free Sleep Calculator — Bedtime & Wake-Up Time | ZzzCalc"
  description="Free sleep calculator and bedtime calculator based on 90-minute REM sleep cycles. Find your ideal bedtime or wake-up time. Wake up refreshed, not groggy."
  canonical="https://zzzcalc.vercel.app"
  keywords="sleep calculator, bedtime calculator, sleep cycle calculator, free sleep calculator, REM cycle calculator, wake up refreshed, what time should I go to sleep, sleep time calculator, bedtime calculator free, sleep calc"
  structuredData={[
    faqStructuredData,
    breadcrumbStructuredData([
      { name: "Home", url: "https://zzzcalc.vercel.app" },
    ]),
  ]}
>
  <Hero />

  <section id="calculator" class="py-6 sm:py-12">
    <div class="container-main">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <Calculator />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 sm:py-20">
    <div class="container-main">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.75;">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight mb-4" style="color: var(--text-page);">
          A sleep calculator built around your biology
        </h2>

        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base">
          If you have ever asked yourself <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">"what time should I go to sleep?"</strong> or <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">"what time should I wake up?"</strong>, the answer is not about a fixed hour — it is about your sleep cycles. Human sleep moves through repeating 90-minute cycles — light sleep (N1, N2), deep slow-wave sleep (N3), and REM — all night long. Waking at the end of a cycle, when your brain is naturally closest to the surface, is the difference between feeling alert and spending the first hour of your day in a fog. That is the principle behind every good <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">sleep calculator</strong>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base mt-4">
          ZzzCalc is a free <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">bedtime calculator</strong> and <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">wake-up time calculator</strong> that works backward from your target wake time — or forward from your bedtime — in 90-minute blocks. It accounts for the average 14 minutes it takes to fall asleep, then shows you every cycle-aligned option from 4 to 6 cycles. Each result includes a quality rating so you can decide what trade-off works for your schedule.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base mt-4">
          Sleep needs change across your lifetime, which is why a proper <strong style="color: var(--text-card);">sleep cycle calculator by age</strong> matters. Teens need 8-10 hours (6-7 cycles), adults need 7-9 hours (5-6 cycles), and seniors often do best with 7-8 hours (5 cycles). ZzzCalc lets you experiment with different cycle counts to find what works for you — whatever your age or schedule.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base mt-4">
          The same math applies whether you are a shift worker planning daytime sleep, a parent working around a newborn, or someone trying to shake off that mid-afternoon slump with a power nap. No account needed. No data tracked. Just the calculation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 sm:py-20" style="background: var(--bg-soft);">
    <div class="container-main">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight mb-6 text-center" style="color: var(--text-page);">
          How to use this sleep calculator
        </h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
          <div class="card-primary text-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-primary);">1</span>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mt-2 mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Choose your mode</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              Select "I want to wake up at" to find your ideal bedtime, or "I'm going to bed now" to calculate your optimal wake time. Enter the time or use the <strong>Now</strong> button for instant results.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-primary text-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-primary);">2</span>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mt-2 mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Set your latency</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              Adjust the <strong>sleep latency</strong> slider to match how long you typically take to fall asleep — from 5 minutes (fast sleeper) to 45 minutes (slow sleeper). The default 14 minutes matches the scientific average.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-primary text-center">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-primary);">3</span>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mt-2 mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Pick your schedule</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              Review your cycle-aligned options — from 4 to 6 cycles — each with a quality rating. Tap any result to see a visual <strong>sleep timeline</strong> showing N1, N2, deep sleep, and REM stages. Copy your chosen time with one tap.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 sm:py-20">
    <div class="container-main">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.75;">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight mb-4 text-center" style="color: var(--text-page);">
          Sleep calculator examples
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-center mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
          Here is what the calculator recommends for common wake-up and bedtime scenarios. Your personal results may vary based on your sleep latency setting.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-3" style="color: var(--text-card);">
              Wake up at 6:00 AM
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Optimal bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">8:46 PM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">6 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Recommended bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">10:16 PM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">5 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Minimum bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">11:46 PM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">4 cycles</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-3" style="color: var(--text-card);">
              Wake up at 7:00 AM
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Optimal bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">9:46 PM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">6 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Recommended bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">11:16 PM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">5 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Minimum bedtime</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">12:46 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">4 cycles</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-3" style="color: var(--text-card);">
              Going to bed at 10:00 PM
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Optimal wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">7:44 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">6 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Recommended wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">6:14 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">5 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Minimum wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">4:44 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">4 cycles</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-3" style="color: var(--text-card);">
              Going to bed at 11:00 PM
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Optimal wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">8:44 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">6 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-card);">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Recommended wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">7:14 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">5 cycles</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5">
                <span style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">Minimum wake time</span>
                <span style="color: var(--text-card); font-weight: 500;">5:44 AM</span>
                <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-primary);">4 cycles</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xs mt-6 text-center" style="color: var(--text-muted-soft);">
          Calculations assume 14-minute sleep latency. Adjust the latency slider in the calculator above for personalized results.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 sm:py-20" style="background: var(--bg-soft);">
    <div class="container-main">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.75;">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight mb-4 text-center" style="color: var(--text-page);">
          Who should use a sleep cycle calculator?
        </h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Early risers and morning people</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              If your alarm goes off at 5:00 AM or 6:00 AM, finding the right bedtime is critical. A <strong>sleep calculator for wake time</strong> tells you exactly when to go to bed so you wake at a cycle boundary — no more groggy 5 AM starts.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Shift workers and night owls</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              Irregular schedules make sleep timing harder. Use the calculator in reverse mode — tell it when you are going to bed and get your <strong>optimal wake-up time</strong> to maximize rest within your available window.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">New parents</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              When your sleep is broken into fragments, every minute counts. A <strong>sleep cycle calculator</strong> helps new parents time their rest between feedings so they wake from naps feeling somewhat restored rather than completely drained.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-primary">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-base sm:text-lg tracking-tight mb-1" style="color: var(--text-card);">Students and busy professionals</h3>
            <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-card-muted);">
              Tight schedules often push sleep to the bottom of the priority list. Use ZzzCalc to find the <strong>best bedtime for your wake time</strong> — whether you need 6, 7.5, or 9 hours — and make every hour of sleep count.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Features />
  <FAQ />
  <ScienceCard />
</Layout>
